  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Production Operator (Manufacturing / Chemical Plant)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities</strong></u>: <br />- Receive, transfer, and store bulk raw materials safely</p><p>- Manage on-site waste handling and coordinate waste removal vendors</p><p>- Collect water samples and support lab testing and release</p><p>- Monitor utilities, equipment, and operating parameters; maintain accurate records</p><p>- Operate forklifts and handle materials and equipment safely</p><p>- Maintain housekeeping and 5S standards across work areas</p><p>- Prepare finished goods containers for shipment and labelling</p><p>- Support and escort external contractors within controlled site areas</p><p>- Comply with HSE policies, procedures, PPE, and hazardous chemical handling requirements</p><p>- Participate in emergency response (CERT), safety activities, and continuous improvement initiatives</p><p>- Complete mandatory training and support overtime or weekend work when required<br /></p><p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u>: </p><ul><li>Practical, hands-on experience in manufacturing operations is required.</li><li>Proficiency in computer use and typing; familiarity with Microsoft Office applications is a plus.</li><li>Collaborative mindset and willingness to support colleagues when needed.</li><li>Experience in areas such as safety, occupational health, quality assurance, environmental management, logistics, and equipment maintenance.</li><li>Familiarity with standards and practices such as ISO 9001, ISO 14001, ISO 45001, SS651, cGMP, and microbial control in manufacturing is advantageous.</li><li>Safety-conscious and quality-oriented attitude.</li><li>Diploma, GCE ‘A’/’O’/’N’ levels, NITEC, or Higher NITEC.</li><li>Forklift license is a plus.</li><li>Knowledge or certification in HAZMAT, firefighting, and incident management is advantageous.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Other Information: </strong></u><br />Working Day: Monday to Friday<br />Working Location: Tuas<br /></p>",
